* Code and Play

* Code and Play

# Use .code command to show code block
# Use .play command to show runnable code block
# Add `-edit` flag to enable edit
# Add `-numbers` flat to show line number

    .code [-edit]? [-numbers]? [-style=<css>]? <file>

.code -edit -numbers code/go.go

.play -edit -numbers code/go.go

Try edit the code and run again.
You can use `SHIFT+ENTER` to quick run when editing.

* Supported Languages

Now we support

- Go
- Java/Groovy
- C/C++
- Python
- Lua
- Perl
- Bash
- JavaScript

To make sure WebPPT can correctly run your code, the code file must have correct extension name.
Or, for script language, you can use shebang flag to specify binary to run the code.

* Play Code

*Go*

.play -edit -numbers code/go.go

*Java*

.play -edit code/java.java

*JavaScript*

.play -edit code/node.js

* Play Code

*C*

.play -edit -numbers code/c.c

*C++*

.play -edit -numbers code/cpp.cpp

*Lua*

.play -edit code/lua.lua

* Play Code

*Bash*

.play -edit code/bash.sh

*Python*

.play -edit code/python.py

*Perl*

.play -edit code/perl.pl

*Groovy*

.play -edit -numbers code/dsl.groovy /START/,/STOP/

# we can control what to show by START and STOP (or any other names are allowed) which is defined in the code file.

* Play Code

*Python with shebang*

.play -edit -numbers code/python-shebang

* Multimedia

* Image

# You can use `.image` command to show image

    .image <url> [<height> <width>]?

Support Formats: `PNG`, `BMP`, `JPG`, `GIF`, `SVG`

.image resources/svg.svg 40 40

.image resources/gif.gif

* Video

# You can use `.video` command to show video

    .video <url> <type> [<height> <width>]?

.video resources/mp4.mp4 video/mp4 400 800

* Formula

# You can use `.latex` command to show complex formula
# You can define several formulas in one file. Each formula should start with `$$<id>` and end with `$$`
# If id is not given, the whole file will be treated as a formula

    .latex <url> [<id>]?

[[welcome/resources/latex.latex][Raw File]]

.latex resources/latex.latex abc

* CSV

# You can use `.csv` command to show table from csv file
# You can specify comma character and comment character.
# By defautl, comma=',' comment='#'

[[welcome/resources/csv.csv][Raw File]]

    .csv [-style=<css>]? [-comma=<char>]? [-comment=<char>]? <url>

.csv -style=height:450px; resources/csv.csv

* HTML and IFrame

* HTML support

# You can use `.html` command to include a html file.

    .html <url>

[[welcome/resources/html.html][Raw File]]

.html resources/html.html

* IFrame support

# You can use `.iframe` command to include a whole website.

    .iframe <url> [<height> <width> <scale>]?

# Scale is an optional integer, unit is %, default is 100, means 100% scale.

.iframe .. 600 1000

* Chart and Graph

* Echarts

# You can use `.echarts` command to show echart.
# You need to provide a js script with echart variable `option`

    .echarts <url> [<height> <width>]?

[[welcome/resources/echarts.echarts][Raw File]]

.echarts resources/echarts.echarts 450 900

* Graphviz

# You can use `.graph` command to show graphviz

    .graph <url> [-scroll|-style <css>] [<height> <width>]?

# -scroll is to show the scroll bar
# -style is to set the css style (not contains space)

[[welcome/resources/graph.graph][Raw File]]

.graph resources/graph.graph 450 900

* UML

# You can use `.uml` command to show PlantUML

    .uml <url>

[[welcome/resources/uml.uml][Raw File]]

.uml resources/uml.uml
